channel.title: I didn't send that email?
channel.description:
Ok, so I get an email from my sister a few minutes ago replying to an email that I never sent her. How do I look up where this email came from?
Here is the email:
From: <removedname> [mailto:<removedname> ] Sent: Tuesday, June 22, 2010 11:17 AM To: [email]<removedname> @gmail.com[/email] Subject: Re: translation
AAAAAAAAAHHHHHHH........ SHALOM??? What are we jewish now?
--- On Tue, 6/22/10, [email]<removedname> @gmail.com[/email] <<removedname> @gmail.com> wrote:
From: [email]<removedname> @gmail.com[/email] <<removedname> @gmail.com> Subject: translation To: [email]<removedname> @yahoo.com[/email] Date: Tuesday, June 22, 2010, 8:06 AM God blessing for your new year of life and today a beautiful birthday I wish you of entire heart SHALOM
Happy Birthday Steph

item.title: I didn't send that email?
item.dc:creator: Katana
item.description:
I will note this has happened at my school as a practical joke before. (I’ll paraphrase, this is from memory)

(first message was something from the professor to a student indicating about academic dishonesty/bad group work etc)

Prof,
I’m sorry if this innocence is sounding faked, but I honestly don’t know what you were talking about. I have contributed everything I can to the group project, and have been sure to use authentic sources. Could I please meet at your office to discuss this? I really can’t take an F on this assignment!

RE:
I’m sorry, but I don’t know which E-mail you’re referring to.

(turned out one of the classmates had played a prank, and spoofed the from and reply-to part of the header. This is technically academic dishonesty in itself, so he was owed a favor to not say anything)

item.title: I didn't send that email?
item.dc:creator: Samapico
item.description:
too long; didn’t read

You’d need the header of the message that SHE received. We could get the ip in there, but that header right there just tells us where her reply went through, so it’s not much help.
But first thing to do (if not already done) would be to change your password… chances are some chinese bot hacked in your account or something. It happened to me with my hotmail account: every single contact of me received a message about some bullshit, and I asked one of them to give me the header, and it traced to China… I hate China.

item.title: I didn't send that email?
item.dc:creator: Seth
item.description:
CatzEyes93:

yep… that was the one that went all emo on facebook.

And for some reason I really dont think someone is “in” my account. It IS her birthday today and I just dont see how some joe schmo off the street would login to my email only to send my sister a happy birthday on the correct day no less. I checked my gmail calendar, and it does not list her birthday (or any other events)

To me it seems like an automated email… but from where did it come from ? What program could possibly send an email from my gmail account?

It is probably a fake addresser. All someone would need is the email address of you and your sister.
